text: Hans Frei or Hans Frey (1450–1523) was a renaissance luthier specialising in lutes, from Nuremberg, Germany. He worked in Bologna, Italy. His instruments survive at the Kunsthistorisches Museum, Vienna, Austria. ==References== Category:Lute makers Category:Luthiers Category:1450 births Category:1523 deaths
